# Prefer `type` over `interface`

Use `type` aliases instead of `interface` declarations for all type definitions.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
interface Props {
  name: string;
  onClick: () => void;
}

// ✅ GOOD
type Props = {
  name: string;
  onClick: () => void;
};
```

For extending types, use intersection (`&`) instead of `extends`:

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
interface ChildState extends ParentState {
  extra: boolean;
}

// ✅ GOOD
type ChildState = ParentState & {
  extra: boolean;
};
```
